        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add session-limit reset confetti celebration",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAdds an opt-in **Session limit confetti** celebration that plays full-screen confetti when a provider's **session** usage resets — mirroring the existing weekly-limit celebration.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"658\" height=\"854\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-28 at 15 55 19\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6d5c9bb6-7680-436f-bf4a-14efd7b38195\" />\r\n\r\nUnder the hood, the weekly-limit reset detector is generalized into a shared limit-reset detector so both the session and weekly plan-utilization series are tracked by the same code path, with separate persisted state per series. The confetti overlay itself is the **existing, unchanged** `ScreenConfettiOverlayController` already used by the weekly celebration — both handlers now route through one shared `playLimitResetConfetti(provider:accountIdentifier:resetKind:)`.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- **Detector refactor** (`UsageStore+PlanUtilization.swift`): rename `WeeklyLimitResetDetectorState` → `LimitResetDetectorState`; `postWeeklyLimitResetCelebrationIfNeeded` now drives a shared `postLimitResetCelebrationIfNeeded` for both `.session` and `.weekly`, with load/persist parameterized by defaults key + series name.\r\n- **Generic session windows**: session-reset detection now also surfaces a 300-minute session lane for the Antigravity and default provider branches (z.ai 5-hour windows, etc.), not just Codex/Claude — so the new setting works for every provider that exposes a session window. (Addresses review feedback below.)\r\n- **Event/notification** (`Notifications+CodexBar.swift`, `UsageStore.swift`): new `codexbarSessionLimitReset` notification + `SessionLimitResetEvent`, with a dedicated `sessionLimitResetDetectorStates` store loaded at init.\r\n- **Setting** (`SettingsStore*.swift`): `confettiOnSessionLimitResetsEnabled` (default **off**) wired through defaults, state, and menu observation.\r\n- **App wiring** (`CodexbarApp.swift`): new observer plus the shared `playLimitResetConfetti(...)` used by both session and weekly handlers.\r\n- **UI + i18n**: new toggle in the Advanced pane; `session_limit_confetti_title/subtitle` localized across all supported languages.\r\n- **Tests**: session reset detection (Codex/Claude **and** generic z.ai session lane) and the new setting are covered.\r\n- **Changelog**: entry added under `0.37.4 — Unreleased`.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\n- `swift build` — succeeds\r\n- `swift test` — full suite passes (all suites green)\r\n- New focused tests:\r\n  - `session quota celebration posts when session usage resets to zero` (Claude)\r\n  - `session quota celebration posts for generic provider session lane` (z.ai)\r\n  - settings persistence for `confettiOnSessionLimitResetsEnabled`\r\n\r\nThe reset→notification→confetti path is covered end-to-end by the unit tests above (they assert a `SessionLimitResetEvent` is posted exactly once on a >threshold→0 transition, gated per series). The confetti overlay is the pre-existing weekly mechanism, so the new code adds detection + the default-off toggle rather than new rendering.\r\n\r\n## Behavior is default-off\r\n\r\nThe setting ships disabled; it only celebrates after the user explicitly opts in under Settings → Advanced → \"Session limit confetti\".\r\n\r\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\r\n",
        "branch": "feat/session-limit-confetti",
